✅ Complete Essential Git Commands
📁 Repository Setup
git init – Initialize a new Git repository

git clone <repo-url> – Clone an existing repository

📥 Staging & Committing
git add filename – Add a specific file to staging

git add . – Add all files to staging

git status – Show current status of files

git commit -m "message" – Commit staged files

git commit --amend – Modify the last commit

📤 Pushing & Pulling
git push – Push changes to remote

git push -u origin main – Push and set upstream branch

git push --set-upstream origin main – Alternative to set upstream

git push --force – Force push (⚠️ use with caution)

git pull – Fetch and merge changes from remote

git fetch – Download commits but don’t merge

🧭 Branching
git branch – List local branches

git branch <name> – Create a new branch

git checkout <branch> – Switch branches

git checkout -b <name> – Create and switch to new branch

git merge <branch> – Merge a branch into current

git rebase <branch> – Reapply commits on top of another base

🌍 Remote Repositories
git remote -v – Show current remote URLs

git remote add origin <url> – Add a remote repo

git remote remove origin – Remove remote repo

🔍 History & Inspection
git log – Show commit history

git log --oneline – Short view of history

git diff – Show unstaged changes

git diff --staged – Show staged changes

git diff commit1-id commit2-id – Show diff between commits

git diff HEAD HEAD~1 – Compare latest commit with one before

git show <commit-id> – Show details of a commit

git annotate filename – Who last modified each line

🔄 Undo / Reset / Fix Mistakes
git reset – Unstage all files

git reset HEAD filename – Unstage a specific file

git restore filename – Discard changes in working directory

git restore --staged filename – Remove file from staging

git reset --soft HEAD~1 – Undo last commit, keep changes staged

git reset --mixed HEAD~1 – Undo last commit, unstage changes

git reset --hard HEAD~1 – Undo last commit, discard changes (⚠️ irreversible)

git revert <commit-id> – Revert a commit safely 
